---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import NewsletterCTA from '../components/NewsletterCTA.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Jacob Allen — real estate investor, student of markets, and builder.">
  <Nav />
  <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 md:py-24">

    <header class="mb-16 text-center">
      <div class="w-28 h-28 mx-auto mb-8 rounded-full bg-(--color-cream-dark) border border-(--color-rule) overflow-hidden">
        <img src="/images/headshot.jpg" alt="Jacob Allen" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink) leading-tight mb-6">About Jacob Allen</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-(--color-ink-light) leading-relaxed text-lg">
      <p>
        Most people are doing everything right and still not getting ahead.
      </p>
      <p>
        Good job. Saving money. 401k contributions. Following the rules.
      </p>
      <p>
        And somehow, actual financial freedom &mdash; the kind where you don't have to check your account before saying yes to something &mdash; still feels out of reach.
      </p>
      <p>
        I spent a long time wondering why. Then I started paying attention to the people who actually got there. Not the ones who looked like they did. The ones who actually stopped needing a paycheck to survive.
      </p>
      <p>
        Almost all of them owned real estate.
      </p>
      <p>
        That was the pattern I couldn't ignore.
      </p>
    </div>

    <hr class="my-16 border-(--color-rule)" />

    <div class="space-y-6 text-(--color-ink-light) leading-relaxed text-lg">
      <p>
        I'm Jacob Allen &mdash; a real estate investor, student of markets and technology, and someone who's been exactly where you are.
      </p>
      <p>
        I didn't grow up wealthy. I didn't stumble into a deal that changed everything overnight. I started learning, made mistakes, bought my first property, made more mistakes, and kept going. I now own 12 doors across Arizona and I'm still learning every single day.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site exists because I wish something like it existed when I was starting out. Not another guru selling a course. Not a highlight reel of wins. Just someone being honest about what's working, what isn't, and what they'd do differently.
      </p>
      <p>
        That's what you'll find here.
      </p>
    </div>

    <hr class="my-16 border-(--color-rule)" />

    <section>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink) mb-10 text-center">What I Write About</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="border-l-2 border-(--color-accent)/40 pl-6">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink) mb-2">Real Estate</h3>
          <p class="text-(--color-ink-light) leading-relaxed">Strategy, how to find deals, creative financing, and what it actually looks like to build a portfolio from scratch.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-2 border-(--color-accent)/40 pl-6">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink) mb-2">Markets & Finance</h3>
          <p class="text-(--color-ink-light) leading-relaxed">How I think about wealth building, macro trends, and what financial freedom really requires.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-2 border-(--color-accent)/40 pl-6">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink) mb-2">AI & Automation</h3>
          <p class="text-(--color-ink-light) leading-relaxed">How technology is changing the game for investors and operators, and how to stay ahead of it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-2 border-(--color-accent)/40 pl-6">
          <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-semibold text-(--color-ink) mb-2">The Meta</h3>
          <p class="text-(--color-ink-light) leading-relaxed">Mindset, decision-making frameworks, and the mental stuff nobody talks about enough.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <hr class="my-16 border-(--color-rule)" />

    <div class="space-y-6 text-(--color-ink-light) leading-relaxed text-lg">
      <p>
        I'm not here to impress you.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm here because I've made expensive mistakes so you might not have to. I share what I'm learning in real time &mdash; not polished retrospectives after everything worked out.
      </p>
      <p>
        If that's the kind of content you've been looking for, you're in the right place.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-t border-(--color-rule) mt-16">
      <NewsletterCTA
        heading="Join the Newsletter"
        subtext="If that's the kind of content you've been looking for, subscribe. One email a week."
      />
    </div>

    <p class="text-center text-(--color-ink-muted) italic font-serif text-lg mt-8">
      Honest. Practical. Still figuring it out.
    </p>

  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
